<br>
Well I decide to do the Coldain Ring quest now as a break from the experience grind to 60. (also will be changing factions once this is completed).<br>
<br>
I ran around all of Eastern Wastes collecting the needed skins only to become aware that I could not train the skill at the guild anymore<br>
<br>
I did the combining of Threads in Velks for a bit and am currently at 24.  I went to UpperGuk and collected 50 swatches to make Silk armor to get to the mid 30's (will make armor tonight).<br>
<br>
Seeing as how rare the HQ Tundra Kodiak Pelts were I would really prefer to be at a comfortable skill level prior to trying to make the blanket.  <br>
<br>
So anyone have any idea?  I checked all the trade boards and I could not find the trivial level for this blanket.<br>
<br>
Nruter<br>
lil Blackguard<br>
Quellious-Ring Warden<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utilnoom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tilnoom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tfc-central.co.uk/ubb/imu2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 9:31:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring skill needed for first Coldain ring?</span><hr size=1> Afaik, the blanket is not no drop and so you can ask a guildie to make it for you.<br>
<br>
I'm not 100% sure on this though. I'd advise you do some research on it first.<br>
<br>
Tils.<br>
54th Garden Tool<br>
Bertoxx<br>
Healers of Norrath <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utilnoom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tilnoom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tfc-central.co.uk/ubb/imu2.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/11/01 9:32:55 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unruter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nruter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 9:36:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring skill needed for first Coldain ring?</span><hr size=1> That would be so much easier, I will check it out!<br>
<br>
Thanks! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unirecnadthetrademaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nirecnad the Trademaster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 9:39:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring skill needed for first Coldain ring?</span><hr size=1> The blanket IS no drop, but if you do the second step of the quest, you can have it chained. I have done this part for myself and others a bunch of times. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utilnoom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tilnoom</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tfc-central.co.uk/ubb/imu2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 9:40:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring skill needed for first Coldain ring?</span><hr size=1> Just checked our references on it.<br>
<br>
The blanket IS no drop, but it can be multi quested.<br>
<br>
Ah well, I was 1/2 right <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
