<br>
Nruter <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utenai.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tenai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 10:28:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring skill needed for first Coldain ring?</span><hr size=1> The blanket is no drop, but is multiable. The skill required to make the blanket is about 60. I have done this for several guildies, I will make the blanket and get the 1st ring, then we will do the 2nd quest, guildie loots the broken axe. I turn in the first ring, then they turn in the axe and get the seoncd ring.<br>
<br>
Tenai Chevalier<br>
58th Knight of Omani<br>
Bertoxx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aleef>Aleef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 11:43:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring skill needed for first Coldain ring?</span><hr size=1> -The blanket was NOT trivial the first time I made it at 36 skill.<br>
<br>
-The blanket WAS trivial the second time I made it with 41 skill.<br>
<br>
At both 36 and 41 skill I was successful in making it.  My skill is in the 50s somewhere, and I've made 7 more blankets for rings since then, and I've never failed.  Hope this helps.<br>
<br>
-Aleef/Simaton <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uirrekmazel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Irrek Mazel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/11/01 1:36:15 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tailoring skill needed for first Coldain ring?</span><hr size=1> I failed the blanket at 49 skill and it was NOT trivial.  At 80 skill I succeeded.<br>
<br>
